  • Package Core

    • Class Core.Board extends javax.swing.JPanel implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • squares

          Core.Square[][] squares
          internal representation of the matrix

        • PADDING

          int PADDING
          margin that the board will have relative to the window

        • rows

          int rows
          how many rows the matrix has

        • cols

          int cols
          how many colums the matrix has

        • matrix3d

          int[][][] matrix3d
          layered matrix sent by user

        • type3d

          char[] type3d
          type of draw requested by user, by layer

        • init

          boolean init
          checks whether the matrix needs initialization. Not used currently.

        • actborder

          boolean actborder
          activates drawing border lines between every cell

        • borderColor

          int borderColor
          color of the border lines between every cell

        • actfreedraw

          boolean actfreedraw
          activates freedraw, assigning a weight multiplier to every sprite

        • freedrawx

          double[] freedrawx
          Horizontal weight. Sets weight for every image. 1 is the normal size. 2 twice the size, 0.5 half the size

        • freedrawy

          double[] freedrawy
          Vertical weight. Sets weight for every image. 1 is the normal size. 2 twice the size, 0.5 half the size

        • actimgbackground

          boolean actimgbackground
          activates using an image as background

        • imgbackground

          java.lang.String imgbackground
          path to the image in the background

        • backgroundColor

          int backgroundColor
          color of the background if there is no image as background

        • colors

          int[] colors
          RGB color pallete for each integer. In the array each position relates to a number in the matrix
          (first position will be the color of number 0 in the matrix, etc.)

        • text

          java.lang.String[] text
          text written in each position relative to the number in the matrix

        • colortext

          int[] colortext
          RBG color pallete for the color of the text. Only if text is enabled.

        • font

          java.awt.Font font
          font used in the text

        • sprites

          java.lang.String[] sprites
          path of the image displayed in each cell relative to the number in the matrix

        • mouseRow

          int mouseRow
          row of last mouse click

        • mouseCol

          int mouseCol
          col of last mouse click

        • currentMouseRow

          int currentMouseRow
          row of last mouse click. Will reset after each check.

        • currentMouseCol

          int currentMouseCol
          col of last mouse click. Will reset after each check.

        • rmouseRow

          int rmouseRow
          row of last mouse click

        • rmouseCol

          int rmouseCol
          col of last mouse click

        • rcurrentMouseRow

          int rcurrentMouseRow
          row of last mouse click. Will reset after each check.

        • rcurrentMouseCol

          int rcurrentMouseCol
          col of last mouse click. Will reset after each check.

        • mouseLayer

          int mouseLayer
          the layer that mouse clicks should reference in a layered matrix

        • boardSprites

          java.util.ArrayList<E> boardSprites
          the list of pixelSprites that will be drawn over the matrixes.

        • useboardSprites

          boolean useboardSprites

        • cl

          java.awt.event.ComponentListener cl
          Redraws board if window size is changed.

        • ml

          java.awt.event.MouseListener ml
          Event handler every time mouse is clicked.
